@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Welcome to Dierentuin";
}

<!-- Eventueel extra CSS -->
<style>
    body {
        background-color: #f1f3f5; /* Zachtgrijze achtergrond */
    }

    .page-header {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #007bff, #6c757d);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 2rem 1rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        box-shadow: 0 3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        text-align: center;
    }

        .page-header h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

    .content {
        background-color: #fff;
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0 3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

        .content h2 {
            margin-top: 0;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .content p {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        ul{
            padding-left: 15px;
        }

    .footer {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        color: #666;
    }
</style>

<div class="container mt-4">
    <!-- Header / Title -->
    <div class="page-header">
        <h1>Welcome to Dierentuin</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="content">
        <h2>About the Project</h2>
        <p>
            Welcome to Dierentuin, a comprehensive zoo management system designed to help you manage animals, enclosures, and categories efficiently. This project is developed by Eric Abrokwah, Deo Arthur Nyann, and Debo Ogunkoya.
        </p>
        <p>
            Our system allows you to perform various actions such as adding, editing, and deleting animals, enclosures, and categories. You can also view detailed information about each animal, enclosure, and category.
        </p>

        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Manage Animals: Add, edit, and delete animals in the zoo.</li>
            <li>Manage Enclosures: Add, edit, and delete enclosures to house the animals.</li>
            <li>Manage Categories: Add, edit, and delete categories for organizing animals.</li>
            <li>View Details: View detailed information about each animal, enclosure, and category.</li>
            <li>Special Actions: Perform actions like Sunrise, Sunset, Feeding Time, and Check Constraints.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <p>
            To get started, use the navigation menu to explore the different sections of the zoo management system. You can start by adding new animals, enclosures, or categories, or by viewing the existing ones.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="footer">
        <p>&copy; 2025 - Dierentuin - Developed by Eric Abrokwah, Deo Arthur Nyann, and Debo Ogunkoya</p>
    </div>
</div>



